Docs.summary: The list of public IPs which the Batch service will use when provisioning Compute Nodes. The number of IPs specified here limits the maximum size of the Pool - 100 dedicated nodes or 100 Spot/Low-priority nodes can be allocated for each public IP. For example, a pool needing 250 dedicated VMs would need at least 3 public IPs specified. Each element of this collection is of the form: /subscriptions/{subscription}/resourceGroups/{group}/providers/Microsoft.Network/publicIPAddresses/{ip}.
